-- Euro Breakup Unlikely, Majority in German Poll Say, Bild Reports
-- B y   A l e x   W e b b
-- 2011-12-30T07:15:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-30/euro-breakup-unlikely-majority-in-german-poll-say-bild-reports.html
A majority of Germans don’t think
the euro currency zone will break up in 2012,  Bild Zeitung
 reported, citing a poll carried out for the newspaper by YouGov.  About 57 percent don’t think the currency will collapse
while 20 percent said a breakdown was likely, the newspaper
reported.  A majority of those questioned also said they weren’t
worried about losing their jobs next year, with 53 percent not
worried at all, 12 percent saying they had “rather big”
worries about becoming unemployed and 28 percent saying they had
“rather small” worries about being out of work, Bild reported.  The newspaper didn’t disclose when the poll was taken or
the number of those surveyed.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Webb  in Frankfurt 
